<subSubSection id="C924843E69150E27677562FC43DDE7F0" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" type="type protologue">
<paragraph id="177D1487B226935A42804CE5E8DEE000" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Type protologue.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE1C7955276F36531153675BB11EEC1E" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">
Ad fontes calidos Araschan Bulak in Turkestania occidentali, 
<emphasis id="3D220E46CC3D651F29152829AA736416" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Krause</emphasis>
s.n. 
<emphasis id="52AA6921AE8813CE8DBDA0E87BE885C0" bold="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Type</emphasis>
: Taschkenter Alatau, Araschan Bulak, 11 Jun 1871, (
<taxonomicName id="7A94534286F35699EA382F0B036031B4" genus="Hieronymous" lsidName="Hieronymous" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD14478A9586698D2A87F2CCC03A1B32" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Hieronymous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<emphasis id="0A259930C375128E54F7D8B73A1F6996" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Krause</emphasis>
s.n. (holotype: LE [only one collection cited]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="62B6C6943047EBDF517C1B9A6A4CBBA9" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" type="notes">
<paragraph id="11FF1A4F6936B858E7E8B977776EAB96" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31F64D447C0D48EB6B6AAD71F189A8A4" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName id="3D6F037F883DA71BA08602843A6338A4" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis id="896179180C69AEB47184D1F9F6486239" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was applied by several authors to small densely tufted alpine annual plants of south-central and southwest Asia, which we recognise as 
<taxonomicName id="88431C7047687DEE87DAD8461EECB155" genus="P." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="P. diaphora var. alpina" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="variety" species="diaphora" variety="alpina">P. diaphora var. alpina</taxonomicName>
(based on 
<taxonomicName id="0F242FC19BA1A66E6BDFF9684561AD4E" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">Poa persica var. alpina</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="56739FE055CA2BB4C793AD43EDCE6198" author="Boissier, PE" editor="Boissier, PE" journalOrPublisher="5. H. Georg, Basilae" pageId="20" pageNumber="89" pagination="432 - 692" refId="B3" refString="Boissier, PE, 1884. Ordo CXLI. Gramineae. In: Boissier, PE, Ed., Flora Orientalis, vol. 5. H. Georg, Basilae: 432 - 692" title="Ordo CXLI. Gramineae." volumeTitle="Flora Orientalis, vol." year="1884">Boissier [1884]</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="B5C088D89A6BF5E1AE64E0673C138998" author="Tzvelev, NN" journalOrPublisher="Botaniceski Zurnal (Moscow &amp; Leningrad)" pageId="23" pageNumber="92" refId="B67" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 1976. Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1-788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" title="Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1 - 788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" year="1976">Tzvelev (1976</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 480) noted that the holotype collection of 
<taxonomicName id="8D725FC374C98FFAEB7C0CA4EC1960B6" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis id="373B30EBC2638B8C4EC6AD2E4BD07E17" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">E. bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared to be a mix of 
<taxonomicName id="65427968858B73B28FE14FFA4EF75E3D" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica">
<emphasis id="1CA93E5E975B35FD48F48932D9BFCF94" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">altaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="B5C8EE9C0026D108126A054F68150E7C" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="diaphora" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="diaphora">
<emphasis id="27FDBDFDEEDFC0F152AEDF648B275E86" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">diaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="48149EB8EC1E0FBDB9F4B58A34125A43" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="songarica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="songarica">
<emphasis id="09A181E8BFCD45C06745EDD7B052E38F" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">songarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms (&quot;p.p. max&quot; = 
<taxonomicName id="A8B573A09ECCAB3A9952D7A695D00F6C" authority="subsp. songarica" family="Poaceae" genus="E." infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica" subspecies="songarica">E. altaica subsp. songarica</taxonomicName>
, somewhat intermediate between this subsp. and subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="ABC1322D7E0F29B6C21B6DEFDB18A51D" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica" subspecies="altaica">altaica</taxonomicName>
, and &quot;p.p. minor&quot; = 
<taxonomicName id="3FFB7BFD8A7AF7DBA27D7D986E77FFFB" authority="subsp. altaica" family="Poaceae" genus="E." infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica" subspecies="altaica">E. altaica subsp. altaica</taxonomicName>
); he considered 
<taxonomicName id="DE365ABDCDF4777B92739D10D6D79B98" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis id="0611163D9E1576D293457CA62070428C" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">E. bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDCA554E42501BB369714E89F50234" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica">
<emphasis id="E2C346C59525C82E26FCFF3EBEBB55B1" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">E. altaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="D8E09D61E0D1CF184740CC099EC0C121" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" subspecies="songarica">songarica</taxonomicName>
. Further study is needed to clarifiy the placement of 
<taxonomicName id="158BD770D9A487FBE74959CF7273BB79" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis id="E19FD8CF990D4989BBC30544ED0BE3ED" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and determine if it is synonymous with 
<taxonomicName id="EBEEC550F855F892F5515244D5043CB2" genus="P." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="P. diaphora var. alpina" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="variety" species="diaphora" variety="alpina">P. diaphora var. alpina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
